"from\": 2922, \"to\": 2929}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Being offended is a symptom of the egoism pandemic in American society.\", \"from\": 2990, \"to\": 3061, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3044, \"end\": 3060, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Culture_of_the_United_States\", \"score\": 0.990141051303, \"rank\": 0.009957115386739412, \"text\": \"American society\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Culture_of_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Culture_of_the_United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a symptom\", \"from\": 3008, \"to\": 3017}, {\"ngram\": \"the egoism\", \"from\": 3021, \"to\": 3031}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Of course the tableau is mocking you - who else in the world is there?\", \"from\": 3062, \"to\": 3132, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the tableau\", \"from\": 3072, \"to\": 3083}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 3113, \"to\": 3122}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Writing a newspaper column as I do, I continually hear from the offended.\", \"from\": 3134, \"to\": 3207, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a newspaper column\", \"from\": 3142, \"to\": 3160}, {\"ngram\": \"the offended\", \"from\": 3194, \"to\": 3206}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Many simply present the simple fact of their offendedness, as if nothing more need be said.\", \"from\": 3208, \"to\": 3299, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the simple fact\", \"from\": 3228, \"to\": 3243}, {\"ngram\": \"their offendedness\", \"from\": 3247, \"to\": 3265}, {\"ngram\": \"nothing\", \"from\": 3273, \"to\": 3280}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Your column offended me, sir.\", \"from\": 3300, \"to\": 3329, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Your column\", \"from\": 3300, \"to\": 3311}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Period.\", \"from\": 3330, \"to\": 3337, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Period\", \"from\": 3330, \"to\": 3336}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The \\\"So do something about it\\\" is unvoiced.\", \"from\": 3338, \"to\": 3381, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"something\", \"from\": 3349, \"to\": 3358}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Though I am not sure what I am supposed to do.\", \"from\": 3382, \"to\": 3428, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Apologize, I suppose.\", \"from\": 3429, \"to\": 3450, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Recant.\", \"from\": 3451, \"to\": 3458, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Recant\", \"from\": 3451, \"to\": 3457}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Because they are offended.\", \"from\": 3459, \"to\": 3485, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I do not do that.\", \"from\": 3487, \"to\": 3504, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"What I want to say is: \\\"Why are you telling me this?\", \"from\": 3505, \"to\": 3557, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I wrote the damn thing.\", \"from\": 3558, \"to\": 3581, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the damn thing\", \"from\": 3566, \"to\": 3580}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Yesterday.\", \"from\": 3582, \"to\": 3592, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Yesterday\", \"from\": 3582, \"to\": 3591}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I believed it then, and believe it even more now, and so should you.\\\"\", \"from\": 3593, \"to\": 3662, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sometimes I write back, \\\"I am not responsible for what you choose to be offended by.\\\"\", \"from\": 3664, \"to\": 3749, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Just to rattle 'em.\", \"from\": 3750, \"to\": 3769, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"'em\", \"from\": 3765, \"to\": 3768}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If they are a scornful Trumpy - are there any other kind?\", \"from\": 3770, \"to\": 3827, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a scornful Trumpy\", \"from\": 3782, \"to\": 3799}, {\"ngram\": \"any other kind\", \"from\": 3812, \"to\": 3826}]}, {\"sentence\": \"- I might type out an email along the lines of, \\\"You know, the opinion of someone in thrall to a liar, bully, fraud and traitor does not carry the weight you seem to imagine it does.\\\"\", \"from\": 3828, \"to\": 4011, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an email\", \"from\": 3847, \"to\": 3855}, {\"ngram\": \"the lines\", \"from\": 3862, \"to\": 3871}, {\"ngram\": \"the opinion\", \"from\": 3887, \"to\": 3898}, {\"ngram\": \"someone\", \"from\": 3902, \"to\": 3909}, {\"ngram\": \"thrall\", \"from\": 3913, \"to\": 3919}, {\"ngram\": \"a liar\", \"from\": 3923, \"to\": 3929}, {\"ngram\": \"bully\", \"from\": 3931, \"to\": 3936}, {\"ngram\": \"fraud\", \"from\": 3938, \"to\": 3943}, {\"ngram\": \"traitor\", \"from\": 3948, \"to\": 3955}, {\"ngram\": \"the weight\", \"from\": 3971, \"to\": 3981}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Then I delete the email before sending - usually, anyway, because any reply from me is something they can wave over their heads as further reason to be offended.\", \"from\": 4012, \"to\": 4173, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the email\", \"from\": 4026, \"to\": 4035}, {\"ngram\": \"any reply\", \"from\": 4078, \"to\": 4087}, {\"ngram\": \"something\", \"from\": 4099, \"to\": 4108}, {\"ngram\": \"their heads\", \"from\": 4128, \"to\": 4139}, {\"ngram\": \"further reason\", \"from\": 4143, \"to\": 4157}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A better reply is, \\\"But I did not write it for you.\\\"\", \"from\": 4175, \"to\": 4227, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A better reply\", \"from\": 4175, \"to\": 4189}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Robert Crumb, the great underground cartoonist, has a wonderful line: \\\"Not everything is for children.\", \"from\": 4228, \"to\": 4330, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4228, \"end\": 4240, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_Crumb\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Robert Crumb\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215